# Combining channels {#tutorial_advanced_combining}

Debug channels can be on or off and they have a label.
Sometimes you might want to write certain debug output to a
debug object when *any* of a given list of debug channels is turned on.
The syntax to do that is based on the fact that debug channels can be viewed upon as a bit mask:
using `operator|`.
In the following example we will write debug output to several different combinations
of the custom debug channels that we defined in the previous paragraph.

